            <thetext>In qooxdoo qx.util.Json has been deprecated, but the parse function of qx.lang.Json is behaving differently with an empty string. The qx.util.Json implementation returns null and the qx.lang.Json throws an exception &quot;SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input&quot;.

This is causing some trouble for me in the conversion. Since changing the behavior of qx.lang.Json.parse() is quite unlikely I think it should at least be documented somewhere, that the behavior will be different.</thetext>
